TODO for '23 edition:
- remove notion of equivalence from slides (and how this relates to other equivalence notions)
- Slightly improved notation for SCMs:
\begin{itemize}
  \item $M^\theta$ : SCM with parameter $\theta$
  \item $M_A$: marginalized SCM $M_{\sm (V\sm A)}$
  \item $M^{[A]}$: subSCM $M$ on $A$
  \item $M^\twin$: twinned SCM
  \item $g^{[A]}_B$: $X_B$ component of solution function of SCM $M^{[A]}$ 
  \item $M^{(1)}$, $M^{(2)}$, $M^{(3)}$, \dots, $M^{(a)}$: indexed SCMs
\end{itemize}
- CI testing: parameter space is \CX_\Theta instead of \Theta, and \CX_\Theta^0 instead of \Theta_0 (and likewise for 1) to allow for the usual distinction between value \theta and random variable \Theta
- CI testing: should now distinguish $P(..\mid \theta)$ from $P(..\mid \Theta)$, and write $P(..\mid \theta)$ rather than just $P(..)$
- changed notation for composing SCMs
